Train Test Split

library(caTools)
sample <- sample.split(df$Private, SplitRatio=0.7)

train <- subset(df, sample==TRUE)
test <- subset(df, sample==FALSE)

Decision tree

library(rpart)
dt.fit <- rpart(Private~., data=train)

# prediction
dt.pred <- predict(dt.fit, newdata=test)

head(dt.pred)
##                                       No       Yes
## Abilene Christian University 1.000000000 0.0000000
## Adelphi University           0.006451613 0.9935484
## Albright College             0.006451613 0.9935484
## Alfred University            0.006451613 0.9935484
## Alma College                 0.006451613 0.9935484
## Alverno College              0.006451613 0.9935484
dt.pred.class <- ifelse(dt.pred[,"Yes"] > dt.pred[,"No"], "Yes", "No")
